11 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
12 Section 1. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 79-32,121 is hereby amended to read as
13 follows: 79-32,121. (a) For tax year 2024, and all tax years thereafter, A
14 taxpayer shall be allowed a Kansas exemption as follows:
15 (1) In the case of married individuals filing a joint return, a personal
16 exemption of $18,320;
17 (2) in the case of all other individuals with a filing status of single,
18 head of household or married filing separate, a personal exemption of
19 $9,160; and
20 (3) in addition to the amount allowed pursuant to paragraph (1) or (2),
21 a personal exemption of $2,320 for each dependent for which such
22 taxpayer is entitled to a deduction for the taxable year for federal income
23 tax purposes.
24 (b) In addition to the exemptions provided in subsection (a),:
25 (1) Any individual filing a federal income tax return under the status
26 of head of household, as defined in 26 U.S.C. § 2(b), shall be allowed an
27 additional Kansas exemption of $2,320 for tax year 2024 and all tax years
28 thereafter; and
29 (2) any individual who has been honorably discharged from active
30 service in any branch of the armed forces of the United States and who is
31 certified by the United States department of veterans affairs or its
32 successor to be in receipt of disability compensation at the 100% rate, if
33 the disability is permanent and was sustained through military action or

