5 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 79-4508a is hereby amended to read as
6 follows: 79-4508a. (a) For tax year 2022, and all tax years thereafter, the
7 amount of any claim pursuant to this section shall be computed by
8 deducting the claimant's base year ad valorem tax amount for the
9 homestead from the claimant's homestead ad valorem tax amount for
10 the tax year for which the refund is sought.
11 (b) As used in this section:
12 (1) "Base year" means the year in which an individual becomes an
13 eligible claimant and who is also eligible for a claim for refund pursuant
14 to this section. For any individual who would otherwise be an eligible
15 claimant prior to 2021, such base year shall be deemed to be 2021 for
16 the purposes of this act.
17 (2) "Claimant" means a person who has filed a claim under the
18 provisions of this act and was, during the entire calendar year preceding
19 the year in which such claim was filed for refund under this act, except
20 as provided in K.S.A. 79-4503, and amendments thereto, both domiciled
21 in this state and was: (A) A person who is 65 years of age or older; or (B)
22 a disabled veteran. The surviving spouse of a person 65 years of age or
23 older or a disabled veteran who was receiving benefits pursuant to this
24 section at the time of the claimant's death shall be eligible to continue to
25 receive benefits until such time the surviving spouse remarries.
26 (3) For tax year 2025 and all tax years thereafter, "household
27 income" means the total Kansas adjusted gross income of all persons of a
28 household in a calendar year while members of such household.
29 (c) A claimant shall only be eligible for a claim for refund under
30 this section if:
31 (1) (A) For tax years 2022, 2023 and 2024, the claimant's
32 household income for the year in which the claim is filed is $50,000 or
33 less, except as adjusted under the cost-of-living adjustment in effect prior
34 to June 30, 2025; and
35 (B) for tax year 2025 and all tax years thereafter, the claimant's
36 household income for the year in which the claim is filed is $80,000 or
37 less; and
38 (2) (A) For base years 2021, 2022 and 2023, the appraised value of
39 the claimant's homestead for the base year is $350,000 or less; and
40 (B) for base year 2024 and all base years thereafter, the appraised
41 value of the claimant's homestead for the base year is $450,000 or less.
42 The provisions of K.S.A. 79-4522, and amendments thereto, shall not
43 apply to a claim pursuant to this section. In the case of all tax years

